"comment_count":17,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"FedericoSchonborn","user_is_author":false,"tags":["rant"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dttagp","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/dttagp/unix_philosophy_is_dead_long_live"},{"short_id":"vvt1fh","created_at":"2026-03-20T21:27:43.000-05:00","title":"What creative technical outlets of yours have been ruined by generative AI?","url":"","score":60,"flags":1,"comment_count":31,"description":"\u003cp\u003eI'm watching over my alma mater's \u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capture_the_flag_(cybersecurity)\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003ecapture the flag\u003c/a\u003e event, and wow, it is dire. This used to be a creative outlet for me and an educational opportunity for students, but now it's almost entirely uncritical use of genAI tools; challenge developers now are \"hardening\" their challenges against this, but this makes it totally inaccessible to new players, so it's losing its educational value and enjoyability as well. As a developer, why should I put any creative effort in when I know it's just going to be churned by a machine and not enjoyed by anyone?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePerhaps I just want to commiserate, but I'm also genuinely curious: what outlets for you have been affected similarly by this new wave?\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"I'm watching over my alma mater's [capture the flag](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capture_the_flag_(cybersecurity)) event, and wow, it is dire. This used to be a creative outlet for me and an educational opportunity for students, but now it's almost entirely uncritical use of genAI tools; challenge developers now are \"hardening\" their challenges against this, but this makes it totally inaccessible to new players, so it's losing its educational value and enjoyability as well. As a developer, why should I put any creative effort in when I know it's just going to be churned by a machine and not enjoyed by anyone?\r\n\r\nPerhaps I just want to commiserate, but I'm also genuinely curious: what outlets for you have been affected similarly by this new wave?","submitter_user":"addison","user_is_author":true,"tags":["ask","vibecoding"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vvt1fh","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/vvt1fh/what_creative_technical_outlets_yours"},{"short_id":"hvq58r","created_at":"2026-03-20T19:11:38.000-05:00","title":"Looking at Unity finally made me understand the point of C++ coroutines","url":"https://mropert.github.io/2026/03/20/unity_cpp_coroutines/","score":8,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"LesleyLai","user_is_author":false,"tags":["c++"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hvq58r","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/hvq58r/looking_at_unity_finally_made_me"}]